entry.title: Add enterprise policy to control whether unload can be deprecated.
entry.content:
This adds a command-line switch

unload-event-handler-deprecation-disallowed that is set on every

renderer if deprecation is allowed.



One tricky point is that it is never set correctly on the browser

process. I think this is OK because the only use for the feature list in the browser is for fenced frames and fenced frames never allow

unload. However this seems like a possible trap in the future. One way

to clean that up would be to stop special casing fenced-frames and

unload in EventTarget::AddEventListenerInternal and instead add a

GetPermissionsPolicyFeatureListForFencedFrame now that unload is

controlled by PP.

entry.title: Fix flaky test in ServiceWorkerProcessBrowserTest
entry.content:
This CL improves the test flakiness of

ServiceWorkerProcessBrowserTest.ServiceWorkerAndPageShareProcess. It

seems the test is flaky because `GetRunningServiceWorkerCount()`

sometimes returns 0, which means the browser process doesn't seee any

running ServiceWorkers.



I believe this is a timing issue. And what this test wants to check is

about the process id. So it makes sense to wait for the SW until

observing the running status before getting process id.

entry.title: Make "CreateShortcut" use document title not web app (manifest) title
entry.content:
With the "kCreateShortcutIgnoresManifest" flag on, the "Create

Shortcut" flow defaults to using the app title found in the web app

manifest (if available) rather than the document title. Using the

document title is consistent with non-app pages and is more sensible

given it is creating a shortcut to the current document, not to the app.

queries Android for apps that can handle a selected text. As part of the

implementation, a set of place holder empty actions are added to the

context menu until ARC asynchronously queries and decide what actions

should be presented to the user.



This set of place holder actions can be visible specially on low

performance devices, this CL makes the set of place holder entries

invisible and inaccessible to the user until the moment we receive the

final set of actions for the user.



Bug: b/292029284

address 3) right click said address and observe/launch 'Maps'

entry.title: Add speech recognition option to skip continuously empty audio
entry.content:
Websites may produce audio streams consisting of nothing but zeroes. We

can improve performance by catching this special case before passing the

audio on to the speech recognition engine.



This CL adds an option to do this to SpeechRecognitionOptions.



The implementation waits for 10 seconds of empty (i.e. all-zero) audio

before skipping subsequent empty audio packets, because brief periods of

empty audio can be meaningful input to the speech recognition engine.
